{"id":"d=origam-topic-2445//p=3ca84b02aa36494282d66d2d2c935dbb","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-2445"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["a900ab1d0c1d409db621615cec58162a"],"__file_part":["f49799bacf23480582feb9bc3dce9c47"],"__part_n":["0"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"category":["docs"],"categoryId":["8"],"topicId":["2445"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/workflow-call-context-mapping/2445"],"title":["Workflow Call Context Mapping"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"# Workflow Call Context Mapping\n\nCategory: docs\nURL: https://community.origam.com/t/workflow-call-context-mapping/2445\n\n@system (2017-12-31 23:00:00Z):\n You can pass data between the caller and the called workflow by adding Context Mapping elements under the Workflow Call element. \n   CONTEXT MAPPING ATTRIBUTES \n \n\n\n\n\n \n \n Direction \n Specifies the direction of the mapping.\n \n \n  Input - The  CallerContextStore  data will be passed to the called workflow\u0027s  TargetContextStore  before the called workflow is started.  \n  Output - After the called workflow finishes, the data from its  TargetContextStore  will be merged back to the  CallerContextStore . The merge type depends on the  OutputType  of the task.  \n  Return - After the called workflow finishes, the data from its  TargetContextStore  will be used as a return value of this task. So the  CalledContextStore  will be ignored and the data will be merged to the context specified by the  OutputContext  of the task itself. The  EndRule  (if any) will be executed on this data.  \n \n  \n \n \n CallerContextStore \n The context of the caller (this) workflow. \n \n \n XPath \n XPath expression, by which you can limit the values transferred to the called workflow (so the XPath will be executed for Input parameters on the  CallerContextStore ). \n \n \n TargetContextStore \n The context store of the target (called) workflow. \n \n \n \n Typically you will pass some contexts to the called workflow ( Direction = Input ) and you use one of the contexts of the called workflow for return values ( Direction = Return ), so the return value can be checked by the  EndRule .","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-04-29T00:23:08"},"vector":[-0.021910617,-0.021046754,-0.061496258,0.04125094,0.0035514545,0.024381056,-0.028024819,-0.00068487466,0.013381674,0.03207575,0.01565824,-0.0116856815,0.034184568,-0.015531075,0.010069956,0.009587707,0.012601701,-0.016987,0.02768091,0.008687895,0.023987187,-0.009707701,-0.010848185,-0.0042803874,-0.010549938,-0.00668306,-0.027291615,-0.047300417,-0.024041034,-0.009937679,0.008988746,-0.013314063,0.02917012,-0.015628377,-0.021497073,-0.023359688,0.004911085,0.013993699,-0.03244571,0.0075022033,-0.0329812,-0.0062909224,0.010354805,0.010596423,0.009171218,-0.024185978,-0.023284856,-0.02589654,-0.006226851,-0.0449248,-0.015475285,0.006793113,0.021951707,-0.048153136,0.0036479258,0.04249028,-0.07664515,-0.05521541,-0.07046141,-0.012673082,-0.020097768,-0.02294866,-0.019145373,0.0022290456,0.004984615,0.014126075,-0.006466412,0.02116537,-0.021672746,-0.0119784195,0.062001433,0.0015083697,-0.029623777,-0.033711705,-0.047298852,-0.02251988,-0.010621134,-0.05080044,-0.009368362,0.01283495,-0.022795858,0.0016509094,0.02886956,-0.005941502,0.0037307614,0.0025449714,-0.024390932,0.024367226,-0.0057915184,-0.0012314168,0.028085278,-0.017896667,0.0053585037,-0.013867982,-0.0134285465,-0.019079225,0.001836498,-0.0051424084,-0.005323256,0.025280073,-0.003717806,0.03098118,0.023055099,0.009193026,-0.048785884,-0.01248356,0.020317106,0.0120379515,0.045006458,-0.04585217,0.03316756,0.037202906,0.036725674,0.016638797,0.0020882282,-0.013800097,-0.002840067,-0.0010385396,0.04928406,0.010942482,-0.0020737073,0.024323145,0.068300486,0.009445045,-0.061419092,-0.024394663,3.2120866E-07,0.05248997,-0.012020428,0.01231285,0.04444414,0.03781326,0.015738796